{"title_page": "The Whole World", "text_new": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Whole World\n| cover      = OutkastTheWholeWorld.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Outkast]] featuring [[Killer Mike]] and [[Joi (singer)|Joi]]\n| album      = [[Big Boi and Dre Present... Outkast]]\n| released   = {{start date|2001|11|27}}\n| format     = [[Compact disc|CD]]\n| recorded   = {{Start date|2000}}\n| studio     =\n| venue      =\n| genre      = [[Alternative hip hop]]\n| length     = 4:55\n| label      = [[Arista Records|Arista]]/[[LaFace Records|LaFace]]\n| writer     = Outkast\n| producer   = [[Earthtone III]]\n| chronology = [[Outkast]]\n| prev_title = [[So Fresh, So Clean]]\n| prev_year  = 2001\n| next_title = [[Land of a Million Drums]]\n| next_year  = 2002\n| misc       = {{Audio sample\n | type        = single\n | file        = The Whole World.ogg\n | description =}} {{External music video|{{Youtube|udmTfK6_aM8|\"The Whole World\"}} }}\n}}\n\n\"'''The Whole World'''\" is the first single released from [[Outkast]]'s first compilation album, ''[[Big Boi and Dre Present... Outkast]]''. The song peaked at number 19 on both the [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]] the week of February 23, 2002 and the [[UK Singles Chart]]. The single features [[Killer Mike]] and [[Joi (singer)|Joi]]. Killer Mike would later go on to provide vocals on the duo's following single, \"[[Land of a Million Drums]]\". The song was written by [[Outkast]] and produced by [[Earthtone III]].\n\nThe song won the [[45th Annual Grammy Awards|2002]] [[Grammy Award for Best Rap Performance by a Duo or Group]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.grammy.com/grammys/awards/winners-nominees/208 |title=Best Rap Performance By A Duo Or Group |website=Grammy.com |date= |author= |accessdate=February 7, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n;UK CD single\n# \"The Whole World\" (featuring Killer Mike) \u2013 4:21\n# \"Rosa Parks\" (album version) \u2013 5:24\n# \"B.O.B\" (radio mix) \u2013 4:18\n\n;12\" vinyl single\n# \"The Whole World\" (radio edit) \u2013 4:21\n# \"The Whole World\" (instrumental) \u2013 4:54\n# \"The Whole World\" (club mix) \u2013 4:57\n# \"The Whole World\" (a cappella) \u2013 4:23\n\n==Charts==\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!Chart (2002)\n!Peak<br/>position\n|-\n{{singlechart|Austria|52|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Flanders Tip|9|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Wallonia Tip|4|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Dutch100|39|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany|30|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|New Zealand|4|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Swedish|26|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Swiss|79|artist=Outkast feat. Killer Mike|song=The Whole World}}\n|-\n|[[UK Singles Chart]]\n|align=\"center\"|19\n|-\n|US [[Billboard Hot 100|''Billboard'' Hot 100]]\n|align=\"center\"|19\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Pop Songs]]\n|align=\"center\"|23\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot R&B/Hip-Hop Songs]]\n|align=\"center\"|8\n|-\n|US ''Billboard'' [[Hot Rap Singles]]\n|align=\"center\"|21\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Outkast}}\n{{Killer Mike}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Whole World, The}}\n[[Category:2001 songs]]\n[[Category:2001 singles]]\n[[Category:Outkast songs]]\n[[Category:Arista Records singles]]\n[[Category:Music videos directed by Bryan Barber]]\n\n{{2000s-hiphop-single-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox song\n| name       = The Whole World\n| cover      = OutkastTheWholeWorld.jpg\n| alt        =\n| type       = single\n| artist     = [[Outkast]] featuring [[Killer Mike]] and [[Joi (singer)|Joi]]\n| album      = [[Big Boi and Dre Present... Outkast]]\n| released   = {{start date|2001|11|27}}\n| format     = [[Compact disc|CD]]\n| 