iss\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|3|31}}\n| AltDate         = April 6, 2019\n| ProdCode        = V134\n| Viewers         = 0.53<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-saturday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-6-2019.html|title=Top 150 Saturday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.6.2019|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|author=[[Mitch Metcalf]]|date=April 9, 2019|access-date=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Tired of children's stories, Gwen tells the class her own scary take on a children's story, but the monster she made up has seemingly come to life.\n| LineColor       = 7EC0EE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 35\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 35\n| Title           = There Are No Hoppy Endings\n| WrittenBy       = Miles Smith\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|21}}\n| AltDate         = April 15, 2019\n| ProdCode        = V135\n| Viewers         = 0.47<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-15-2019.html|title=Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.15.2019|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|author=[[Mitch Metcalf]]|date=April 16, 2019|access-date=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortSummary    = Chef struggles to maintain his sanity when the kids continue to blame a stuffed rabbit named Hoppy for everything bad they do.\n| LineColor       = 7EC0EE\n}}\n{{Episode list\n| EpisodeNumber   = 36\n| EpisodeNumber2  = 36\n| Title           = Too Much of a Goo'd Thing\n| WrittenBy       = Laurie Elliott\n| OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2019|4|27}}\n| AltDate         = April 22, 2019\n| ProdCode        = V136\n| Viewers         = 0.46<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.showbuzzdaily.com/articles/showbuzzdailys-top-150-monday-cable-originals-network-finals-4-22-2019.html|title=Top 150 Monday Cable Originals & Network Finals: 4.22.2019|work=[[Showbuzz Daily]]|author=[[Mitch Metcalf]]|date=April 23, 2019|access-date=October 30, 2019}}</ref>\n| ShortS